# Ansible Argument: Single Quotes vs Double Quotes

When passing arguments to Ansible from the command line, you can use either single or double quotes. Here’s how you can pass a message argument to the debug module:

ansible all -m ansible.builtin.debug -a 'msg="welcome to ansible"'

**Using double quotes (requires escaping inner quotes):**

ansible all -m ansible.builtin.debug -a "msg=\"welcome to ansible\""


 **Tip:**  
Single quotes are often easier because you don’t need to escape the inner quotes.

